<refnamediv>
<refname>Old-Fashioned errno Handling</refname>
<refpurpose>A few tricks which operate on the same type as errno, an int.</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv id="gsk-gskerrno.synopsis" role="synopsis">
<title role="synopsis.title">Synopsis</title>

<synopsis>
<link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>            <link linkend="gsk-errno-is-ignorable">gsk_errno_is_ignorable</link>              (<link linkend="int">int</link> errno_value);
<link linkend="int">int</link>                 <link linkend="gsk-errno-from-fd">gsk_errno_from_fd</link>                   (<link linkend="int">int</link> fd);
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>









<refsect1 id="gsk-gskerrno.description" role="desc">
<title role="desc.title">Description</title>
<para>
Methods to determine in an errno is important, and to extract
it from a file-descriptor that had an error.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="gsk-gskerrno.details" role="details">
<title role="details.title">Details</title>
<refsect2 id="gsk-errno-is-ignorable" role="function">
<title>gsk_errno_is_ignorable ()</title>
<indexterm zone="gsk-errno-is-ignorable"><primary sortas="gsk_errno_is_ignorable">gsk_errno_is_ignorable</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>            gsk_errno_is_ignorable              (<link linkend="int">int</link> errno_value);</programlisting>
<para>
Determine whether an errno code is insignificant.</para>
<para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>errno_value</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> errno value.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term><listitem><simpara> whether the error is a transient ignorable error.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="gsk-errno-from-fd" role="function">
<title>gsk_errno_from_fd ()</title>
<indexterm zone="gsk-errno-from-fd"><primary sortas="gsk_errno_from_fd">gsk_errno_from_fd</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="int">int</link>                 gsk_errno_from_fd                   (<link linkend="int">int</link> fd);</programlisting>
<para>
Query the file descriptor for the last error which occurred on it.</para>
<para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>fd</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> a file descriptor.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term><listitem><simpara> the errno code for the last error on the file descriptor.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>

</refsect1>




